Progress Report, Week Ten
entry.content:
This week, I was able to modify the CSS file to my website, so that the site was able to fit the screen fully, and I adjusted the font size do to the change in dimensions of the site's size. I also added a Reverb section to the Amplifiers, so that the user understand what it is, what it is used for, and why guitarists use it when they do. Also, I wrote my Final Report describing my project in full detail based on my Project Objectives that I wrote out before I started my project at the beginning of the quarter, and I prepared my PowerPoint presentation and practiced how I am going to present it, along with my site on Tuesday during lab night to the 2018 BAS-IS cohort.

I spent fourteen hours on my project making a grand total of one hundred and twenty six hours total on my project this quarter.

entry.title: Journal Entry, Week Ten
entry.content:
Evaluate the success of your senior project.

I feel like my senior project was very successful and I included everything a person/the user that goes onto my website should know when first learning about guitar. It might just be basic information about five different guitars and accessories, but each of them are very important in the world of guitar. I am very proud of my site, it really shows off my HTML/CSS skills, and all my knowledge of guitars after playing for almost fifteen years. 

I was also able to learn some new things about some of the guitars along the way that I didn't know before; for instance, I learned the founder of Fender, Clarence Leonidias Fender went by his middle name Leo, and that there were reverse tension type guitars before Reverse Tensions Guitars came out with a full line of those types of guitars. 

Reflect on what was most effective and what was most challenging.

I feel like the most effective part of my project was that I included information that all users (guitar players/non-guitar players) will be able to understand, and I also think the guitar sound samples will help the user differentiate between the types of guitars because each guitar type has a very different sound. Finally, I feel like another effective thing about my project is that I included a reference page for if the user want to learn more about other guitars that I may have not mention on my site. 

As for the most challenging part of my project, I can say that was trying to figure out which types of guitars and accessories to provide information for on my site because when I first started I had a good amount of guitars to choose for, and for the most part I kept the original guitar model that I chose in the beginning for my project. However, I had to change a few along the way if I couldn't find enough information on the guitar/accessory or an aspect of the product I want to include on my site like a sound sample.

entry.title: Progress Report, Week Nine
entry.content:
I finished my project this week, I am very proud of how it turned out. I feel like it has all I wanted to include in it when I first started the website and have to admit, even a little extra with the different guitar and and accessory samples. I think that really helps the user understand why each guitar and accessory is so special and has so much significance to us as guitarists. I hope the resources page helps the user(s) by providing more information on every guitar and accessory that is out there in the world of guitars, acoustic and electric. I was able to finally find a sound sample of the Silvertone Model 1449 guitar, so I reverted and put that page back into my site. 

This week, I worked a total of twelve hours on my project, being the grand total up to one hundred and twelve hours so far this quarter. 

In the next week, I plan to export my project and start working on putting together a PowerPoint presentation to present it to the BAS-IS 2018 cohort next Tuesday during our scheduled lab nine. I will let you know how it goes, good or bad, in the whole scheme of things; I can say am proud of how my project turned out. I also plan to work on getting my final deliverables put together into a zip file, so I am ready for my presentation next Tuesday, and also put together my Final Report that reflects the objectives of my project in a detailed way.

entry.title: Journal Entry, Week Nine
entry.content:
Seek outside evaluation of your project: discuss it with a classmate or person outside of BASIS program and collect their input and feedback.

Post an overview of the discussion.

I showed by project to my grandma because I told her about my project and she was curious on how I was doing on it. She was shocked on how much information I actually provided on the site and thought it was enough for non music and non guitar people to understand. One thing she liked is how easy it is to navigate through the site. She also liked how I provided a picture of each guitar and accessory because she never knew what the difference of each guitar was. She also enjoyed hearing the different samples of each guitar.
 
What was the most valuable thing you learned from that evaluation?

I learned that I have just enough information in order for the ordinary user that knows nothing about guitars that they will learn something from my site. Also that the sound samples were a huge hit.

entry.title: Progress Report, Week Eight
entry.content:
This week, I feel like I got a lot accomplished on my project. I was able to find a playing sample of the reverse tension guitar, however I wasn't able to find one for the Silvertone Model 1449. Although, I did find a sound sample of another Silvertone model guitar, and that was the Silvertone Rocket. That's the page I will replace the 1449 page with, and I will work on writing that page this coming week. I was also able to finish the Straps page and also worked on the Picks page a little bit.

In the coming week, I plan to finish the Picks page and also write the Silvertone Rocket page. I don't think that won't take me that long because I was able to find enough information this week looking at the different sound samples.

This week, I worked on my project for fifteen hours; making one hundred total hours this quarter.

entry.title: Journal Entry, Week Eight
entry.content:
Write a journal entry that addresses these points: two weeks ago, your journal prompt laid out a professional networking strategy with some immediate tasks; discuss what progress have you made on them.

After I came up with my network strategy, I made progress on my strategy right away because I am obviously been a kind person to everyone around me and everyone I meet on a daily basis. I am still working on develop thick skin because I have always been a shy person, and you can make some progress over night, thought. Also, I have started to speak up for myself more often.

As for my job search plans and immediate goals, I ended up not getting the job I applied for. The reason I didn't get the job is because the interviewers thought I needed to get more project experience, which I understood. On the positive side, they did let me know that they would keep my resume on file and let me know if any other job like the one I applied for comes available in the future. Although, I am upset that I didn't get the job, I know things happen for a reason and the right job is still out there, I just have to find it.

entry.title: Progress Report, Week Seven
entry.content:
This past week, I worked on the Straps sub-page on the Accessories page. I was able to find samples of the Gibson Les Paul and the Martin D-28 to give the user a sample of what the guitar sounds like when they play it. I have to admit that I like how clean the D-28 sounds when it is plugged into an amplifier. I am still looking for sound samples of the Reverse Tension Guitar, and the Silvertone Model 1449. Its driving me crazy that those are the only guitar samples I can't find, but I will keep looking. 

In the coming week, I will plan to work on making the final touches on the Straps page and start looking at completing the Picks page. I also plan to keep searching for those guitar sound samples.

This week, I worked a total of ten hours on my project; making a grand total of eighty five hours this entire quarter.

entry.title: Journal Entry, Week Seven
entry.content:
Review and update the contents of your portfolio on the cohort's portfolio website.

Write a journal entry that explains why you are choosing the projects you are choosing for your portfolio. You should identify at least 4 projects for your portfolio.

For the cohorts portfolio website, I have decided to include four different projects that I have worked on while attending Olympic College and while Ive been in the BAS-IS program. The projects include the BAS-IS 2018 cohort portfolio website, my database comparison project, the video game industry wiki page, and my Guitars Galore static website.

1.     When I worked on the BAS-IS 2018 cohort portfolio website during the Fall 2016 and Winter 2017 quarter for my IS Foundations and Information Systems Integration classes. It was a group project; I was the person that was in charge of creating and maintaining the database for the site.

2.     When I worked on my database comparison project during the Winter 2017 quarter of the BAS-IS program. The whole aspect of this project was to compare and contrast five different types of database programs. I chose to look at the similarities and differences between rational and non-rational databases; almost all were relational, except one. The relational databases I looked at were Microsoft Access, MariaDB, Oracle 11g, and MySQL. The only non-relational database I looked into for the project was MongoDB. During the project, I was surprised to find out that most of the databases used C and C++ as their primary programming languages, and also used the commands of SELECT, FROM, WHERE, INSERT, DELETE, etc.

3.     When I worked on the video game industry wiki project for my Digital Economy class in Spring of 2017, it was also a group project that all members were tasked to contribute to each page on the wiki. Some of the pages included an Analysis of the Video Game Industry, Critical Success Factors and Industry Today Reports; also, Leadership and Technology Notes.

4.     The current project I am working on this quarter (Spring 2018), is my Guitars Galore static website. It is just an information website that gives the user information about didnt models of guitars; also, about different accessories a guitarist uses while playing guitar. I have even included a resources page for people who are looking for more information on if they want to purchase a guitar and start learning how to play after viewing my site.

entry.title: Progress Report, Week Six
entry.content:
I made exceptional progress this week, I modified/finished the Amplifier sub-page of the Accessories page, updated picture on about page to match the models of the guitars I covered on my site. I also updated the resources by adding some more amp and capo companies that people can check out if they want to learn more and maybe purchased one if they are interested in doing that. Finally, I adjusted the size of my website, so that it fits the entire with of the browser and so that the pages arent so long when you look at them. One problem I am having, I cant find samples of some of the guitars (specifically, the Reverse Tension, Silvertone, and Martin). I will keep looking, but I will definitely keep the information I already have on all three guitars. This week I worked on my project for a total of fifteen hours, making my grand total so far for the quarter seventy five hours. 

In the coming week, I plan to work on straps and picks pages and continue to make any adjustments to any of the pages as I see fit because there is always room for improvements even if you didnt plan on them in the first place.

entry.title: Journal Entry, Week Six
entry.content:
What is your professional networking strategy?

My professional networking strategy is to start developing thick skin and stand up for myself more because lately and in the past I have been the person that goes along with what is going on around me and I am known to be a very shy person. I know I need to start speaking up for myself and state what my true feeling are. I have been told that a lot over the years, and have tried to make an effort, but it hasn't really surfaced yet. Another thing to do is be nice to everyone I meet; I have always been a nice person and been polite to everyone around me, but I feel like this is a very important trait that I plan to continue to have over the course of my life.

What are your job search / refinement plans?
 
After last weeks, Career Center talk during lab, I actually went to a home owners business to give them my resume and ended up getting an interview with the president and the person that listed the job. I had the interview yesterday and I believe it went well. I have all the qualifications that they are asking for and I smiled because I was happy to be at the interview and being that much closer to getting in to the job force,

Identify clearly the first step, to be done in the next 2 weeks. You will revisit this in your week 8 Journal Entry. 

The first thing I plan to do is keep in touch with the people I had the interview with and just see if I get the job or not. I really hope I get it!

entry.title: Progress Report, Week Five
entry.content: Unfortunately, I wasn't able to accomplish all of what I wanted to get completed this week, but I still got a lot done. I was expecting to work on the Accessories sub-pages and finish most, if not all of the pages completed. The things I got done this week include, I added more resources to the Resources page of the website (links to amplifier and capo stores) if people want to purchase one to advance their guitar skills. I also decided to Replace the SG guitar information page with Reverse Tension Guitars, so that I have more of a variety in both acoustic and electric guitars (two of each). I modified the Capos page that is part of the accessories to give people more information on what a capo is and what it does; also some capo types that exist out there in the world of guitars, and I started to work on the Amplifier (Amps) page that part of the Accessories page. I plan to work on finishing the Amps page, and start working on the Straps and Picks page (explaining what each is). This week I spent a total of eighteen hours on my project this week, so adding that to my total hours spent this quarter, I'm up to sixty hours.

entry.title: Journal Entry, Week Five
entry.content:
Write a journal entry that reflects on the career center talk at the week 5 lab.  If you can, make a visit to the actual career center as well, and see what they can do for you now. Make an appointment with yourself to use their services before you graduate - your fees go to supporting them, and they have a great collection of services to offer. Even if you have the most perfect resume, they can still help you brush it up. If you are already working in IT, it doesn't hurt to keep that resume up to date!

My reflections of the career center talk that we had during week 5 lab are that it is good to have a unique resume to make yours stand out from other applicants that are also apply for the job you are trying for. I also learned that it is important to avoid what you want out of the resume. For example, you want to avoid saying, I want this type of job and I want to be able to use these skills to do it. I thought this made a lot of sense for going into the job force because the company you are applying for is looking for people with your skills; not you looking for your dream job of this, and you want to not use objectives with, instead you want to put on a summary of interesting facts about yourself. This was the most interesting fact because I was also taught to put objectives of the different specific points in the job of why you are applying for. Another point that caught my eye was that on a resume,  you dont want to list that much of your work experience, so only list 10-15 years in the past. Finally, I was also surprised, but it did make sense, that you dont to put the year you graduated high school because it distinguishes the amount of work experiences you have, and most employers take your work experience by your age.

We also talked about in the meeting was about the take always you need from the job interview process. First, you have to be punctual, and be on time, or at least 15 minutes early for you job interview to show employer that you are ready to work and makes them think, if they are on time for the interview they will be on time for the job they are applying fot. Another thing that is very important are some of the questions they might ask during the interview, and they include, Tell me about your strengths/weaknesses, and why should we have you working for our company? You want to make it more of a memorable conversation, so they will take the consideration of hiring you. Finally, I know you want to dress nice to sell yourself to the potential hires. One thing that I thought was interesting is that you dont want to wear cologne to an interview because you dont want to smell/stink and over power the smell during the interview because I wear cologne all the time, but I dont wear a lot and it makes you more aware of how much cologne you do wear at one time. As you can see, I learned a lot from the career center talk and will definitely take the points mentioned into consideration when in a job interview or when looking for employment.

entry.title: Progress Report, Week Four
entry.content:
This week, I feel like I got a lot accomplished on my project website. I was expecting to get the rest of the Guitar Models sub-pages (Gibson Les Paul, Epiphone, Silvertone, Martin) completed, and I did just that. I also got the "Capos" sub-page done on the Accessories page completed as well. I ran into one issue this week, I had to trash/get rid of the Ibanez Talman sub-page on the Guitar Model page and replace it with a page about the new page about information about the SG guitar model from the guitar company, Epiphone because I could not find that much information on the Talman that would enough for my project. On the other hand, I found enough information about the Epiphone SG that could be enough for my project.

In the next week, I plan to continue and hopefully finish the Accessory sub-pages; of not, get most of them finished. This week, I spent twenty hours working on my project and doing all the research for each guitar/product; that makes a total of forty two total hours on my project so far this quarter.

entry.title: Progress Report, Week Three
entry.content:
I have made significant progress on my Guitars Galore static website project this week. I was expecting to write out some of the information for some of the guitars, and that's exactly what I did, and I got even more done than I expected. Some of the things I got done this week are I finalized the description on the About page of the website, and I also finalized the Resources page; I might tweak the two pages in the next couple weeks, if needed before the project is due. Other things I got done are I linked every guitar I have listed on the guitar models page on a separate page for their own information and picture. I also did the same for the Accessories page for the site. Finally, I made some modification to the site as I saw fit and will continue to do this until I feel the website looks perfect or how I want it to look. I have not ran into any issues, and will keep you updated if I do.

In the next week, I plan to add more information and pictures to each of the guitar models and accessories pages and hopefully have it almost finalized by the end of this week. This week, I spent over twelve hours doing all the tasks I listed above. That makes the total hours of the project adding the twelve hours from this week, and ten hours spent on the project thus far, it makes a total of twenty two hours so far this quarter.

entry.title: Journal Entry, Week Three
entry.content:
What are your personal/professional IT strengths (technical and soft skills)?

My technical IT strengths are in programming with Hyper Text Markup Language (HTML), Cascade Style Sheets (CSS), and JavaScript (JS); also, in databases, and networking. I have been using Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, and Excel since I was little. I am proficient on Windows and Macintosh operating systems, and am fimiliar with the Linux/Unix and Cisco environments. Some of my soft skills are I am a fast learner, hardworking, dependable, and I work well with others. 

What are your professional IT goals? Be CLEAR, and include at least 1 immediate goal (0-1 year) and 2 long term goals (5-10 years out).

My immediate goal is to get a good stable job after I graduate and also be earn some certification(s) through Olympic College because I have most of the classes that are required for some certifications in the Web Development side, and want to be able to earn a few certifications, so I can have the upper hand when it comes to getting a job. One of my long term goals is to be able to continue enhancing my skills over the next 5-10 years because has been said that you can learn new things everyday. My other long term goals is to once I get a job, I plan to work towards getting a promotion because I want to prove my skills and that I am willing to work hard for any position in the company.

How well do your strengths and goals align?

I believe that my strengths and goals align perfectly because my skills, both technical and soft, will help me be successful in the long run because each of my technical skills and knowledge will help me get into the IT industry right out of college, and my soft skills will help me in the work environment.

entry.content:
I made progress on my project this week because I got what I wanted to completed done. The things I wanted to get done were have a running website. In result, I got all the pages of my site. They are just rough sketches right now; in the weeks to come, I plan to fine tune every page.

entry.title: Journal Entry, Week Two
entry.content:
What is your project? Describe it as if you had an elevator ride to do it in.
My project is going to be a static website, which just means that it just uses Hyper Text Markup Language (HTML), Cascade Style Sheets (CSS), and some JavaScript; not connected to a database or computer server. The user will only be able to view it on their own computer system, not over the internet. The website will be an information-based website that gives the user some extra resources of what types of makes and models there are of guitars out there. It will be a multi-page site with a home page, a guitar models page, a guitar accessories page, and a reference page for if the user is thinking about purchasing a guitar to start learning how to play.  

What do you know about it? 
I know many different facts about multiple guitars because I have been playing for over fourteen years now and have become very familiar with the different makes and models. I also have been a music fan in general all my life, it seems like. I will let the user in on the difference between each model and why theres not only one type of guitar to use because once I learned that I was very fascinated with why that is.

What will you need to learn to accomplish it? 
For my project, I will not have to learn anything new or different, I will just take the skills I have learned while here at Olympic College the past four years, and the skills I have learned in the BASIS program the past two years. I am excited to show people the skills I have learned within a website that I create from scratch about something that I am very passionate about.

How does it represent your BASIS learning and IT skills?
My project will represent all of the things I learned about HTML, CSS, and JavaScript from the information system (IS) and Computer Information System classes I have taken at Olympic College, including the following: Intro to the Internet (CIS 115), Programming Concepts (CIS 141), Survey of Computing (CIS 150), Intro to HTML (CIS 155), Web Multimedia (CIS 156),  User Interface Design (CIS 160), Beginning Photoshop (DMA 120) to make cool images for my website , IS Foundations (IS 300), Information System Integration (IS 302), and Scripting for Automation (IS 305).

entry.title: Journal Entry, Week One
entry.content:
Write a journal entry that addresses your expectations for this class.

My expectations for this class is to be able to create a project showcasing what skills I have learned while in the Bachelors of Applied Science in Information Systems, most commonly known as, the BAS-IS program here at Olympic College the last two years. I plan to make a website for my project that uses Hyper Text Markup Language (HTML), Cascading Style Sheets (CSS), and maybe some JavaScript mixed in because over the course of this program I have gained a fasination for the web development side, mostly front-end of the Computer Information Systems (CIS) industry. 

Im planning for the concept of my website to be an information site that gives people an opportunity to learn about different types of guitars, and give the website a name of Guitars Galore. I have wanted to create a website about guitars for a while now, and this project I hope can accomplish that, while displaying my knowledge in how HTML, CSS, and JavaScript all function together in creating a cool site that people can visit to learn more about guitars and the history behind the design of some of them. Im not planning to do facts on every guitar ever made, but I might choose a few (like 4-5) of my favorites and write about them.

As for the look, I plan to do a sketch on what I want the site to look like: have a few buttons on the home page that are labeled home, guitars, facts, and maybe add a button for purchasing a guitar from a guitar shop near them, if the user is interested in learning on how to play guitar. I will also create my own logo for the site to personalize it. Some things may change in the process of the project, but that is what I plan for the site to be for the project as of now, while I am still in the beginning stages of my project.  I will try to have the sketch of the outline of the site and logo completed and uploaded to this blog by my first progress report on Tuesday, April 10, 2018. I am looking forward to working on my website and showing it to you as I work on it along the way.
